  <title translate="true">Maximum Leaching Requirement Pane</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Maximum Leaching Requirement Pane</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Farm_Crop_Properties_Dialog_Bo" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Land Use Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">CROP_MAX_LEACHING_REQUIREMENT</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The maximum leaching requirement is 1.0, but this could result in a division by zero (RHOADES equation). It may be any value between 0.0 and 0.9999. This allows the user to specify a maximum allowed leaching requirement. If not specified then it is set to 0.99</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
